     ,"INC-SPECT":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4code":null
	,"x4freetext":["A beam of 238U47+ at an energy of 2.05 GeV (8.6"
		,"MeV/nucleon) was delivered by the ATLAS accelerator."
		,"The average beam intensity was ~10**6 pps, with a"
		,"total integrated beam dose of around 5.5x10**11 ions."]
	}
      ]
     ,"FACILITY":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4codes":[{"code":"LINAC", "dict":"FACILITY", "idict":18,"hlp":"Linear accelerator"}
	    ,{"code":"1USAANL", "dict":"INSTITUTE", "idict":3,"hlp":"Argonne National Laboratory, Argonne, IL, United States of America"}]
	}
      ]
     ,"DETECTOR":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4codes":[{"code":"SI", "dict":"DETECTOR", "idict":22,"hlp":"Silicon detector"}
	    ,{"code":"MWPC", "dict":"DETECTOR", "idict":22,"hlp":"Multi-wire proportional counter"}]
	,"x4freetext":[" A four-sided position-sensitive silicon"
		,"array. Four fission detection arms were positioned"
		,"around 1 m downstream of the target, two at 15"
		,"degrees to the beam axis and two at 10 degrees to"
		,"maximize the acceptance of light and heavy fragments."
		,"Each of the arms had a position-sensitive multiwire"
		,"proportional counter (MWPC) followed by a gaseous"
		,"axially segmented Bragg detector. On an"
		,"event-by-event basis, the Bragg detector yielded the"
		,"total and specific energy loss of any detected"
		,"fragments, and the MWPCs gave their position at the"
		,"entrance to the Bragg detectors."]
	}
      ]
     ,"SAMPLE":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4code":null
	,"x4freetext":["A deuterated polyethylene (CD2) target. Owing to"
		,"target damage from the heavy beam, 11 CD2 targets"
		,"were used during the experiment with thicknesses"
		,"between 410 and 590 microg/cm2. Data were also"
		,"collected with a pure natC target (thickness 584"
		,"microg/cm2) to evaluate backgrounds arising from"
		,"multinucleon transfer-induced fission reactions on"
		,"carbon in the CD2 target."]
	}
      ]
     ,"METHOD":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4code":null
	,"x4freetext":["The experiment was carried out using HELIOS at ANL"
		," (Solenoidal spectrometer for transfer reaction"
		,"studies: HELIOS). The fission-barrier height of 239U"
		,"has been determined via the 238U(d,pF) reaction in"
		,"inverse kinematics. Downstream of the target, a"
		,"Faraday cup was used to measure beam current, and an"
		,"annular silicon detector was used to detect"
		,"elastically scattered deuterons for a narrow range of"
		,"c.m. angles between 29 and 29.3 degrees. The latter"
		,"allows an absolute normalization of measured yields"
		,"to generate absolute cross sections."]
	}
      ]
